avorite pupil of Notker III (Notker der Deutsche). This volume seeks to critically reevaluate earlier research and to open new perspectives on his diverse works as seen from various disciplinary perspectives (German studies, Middle Latin studies, historiography, and musicology), with a special focus on the German glosses attributed to him and on his renowned Casus Sancti Galli.  aEkkehart IV. von St. Gallen (ca. 980 - ca. 1060) war der Lieblingsschüler Notkers des Deutschen. Der vorliegende Band zieht ein kritisches Resümee der bisherigen Forschung und eröffnet neue Perspektiven auf sein vielgestaltiges Werk aus verschiedenen disziplinären Blickwinkeln (Germanistik, Mittellatinistik, Geschichts- und Musikwissenschaft), insbesondere zu den ihm zugeschriebenen deutschsprachigen Glossen und seinen berühmten Casus St. Galli.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aEkkehard (IV.). 4aGlosse. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aApostille.  aEkkehard IV.1 aBrunner, Karl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenhut, Heidi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGlauch, Sonja, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrotans, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHellgardt, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlaper, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrotz, Elke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKössinger, Norbert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeithe-Jasper, Helena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLenz, Philipp, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/c